quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  27,1,"Ta'. Sin. These are the verses of the Qur'an and a Clear Book;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  27,2,"a guidance and good tidings for the believers"{1},footnotes:1:1
  27,3,"who establish Prayer and give Zakah, and have firm faith in the Hereafter."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  27,4,"As for those who do not believe in the Hereafter, We have made their deeds seem attractive to them so they stumble around in perplexity."{1},footnotes:1:1
  27,5,"It is they for whom a grievous chastisement lies in store; it is they who shall be the greatest losers in the Hereafter."{1},footnotes:1:1
  27,6,"As for you, (O Muhammad), you are receiving the Qur'an from the Most Wise, the All-Knowing."{1},footnotes:1:1
  27,7,"(Recount to them) when Moses said to his family: "I perceive something like fire: soon will I bring to you some information from there, or I will bring you a burning brand that you may warm yourselves.""{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  27,8,"But when Moses came to the fire, a call was sounded: "Blessed is He Who is in the fire and whatever is around it. Glory be to Allah, the Sustainer of all in the Universe."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  27,9,"O Moses, verily this is Me, Allah, the All-Mighty, the All-Wise!"
  27,10,"Now cast your rod!" But when he saw the rod writhing as though it were a serpent, he turned his back in retreat and did not even look behind. "O Moses, have no fear. Messengers have no fear in My presence,"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2